lead_paragraph: Alex Lindahl, a high school senior in Michigan, received 40 stitches to his eye after a vaulting pole snapped and became impaled in his orbital bone during a track meet in Dexter.

headline.main: High School Pole Vaulter Sustains Bizarre Injury

abstract: High school pole-vaulter Alex Lindahl receives 40 stitches to his eye after pole snaps during track meet in Dexter, Mich.
